in 1669. Pierre-Paul Hébert/Hubert from France married Suzanne Laporte in QC <i>c.</i> 1716. — This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of South Carolina."]}]},{"name":"Laurence","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a French form of Latin <i>Laurentius</i> ‘man from Laurentum’. <i>Laurentum</i> was a town in Latium, which may have got its name from Latin <i>laurus</i> ‘laurel’, although it is more probably of pre-Roman origin. The given name was moderately popular in the Middle Ages (when it was used for girls as well as boys), under the influence of a 3rd-century saint who was one of the seven deacons of Rome. He was martyred in  258 . The legend is that, having been required to hand over the Church's treasures to the civil authorities, he assembled the poor and sick and presented them. For this act of Christian defiance, he was roasted to death on a gridiron. In England the name is also associated with  St Laurence of Canterbury  (  d. 619 ). A more recent influence has been the actor  Sir Laurence Olivier  (  1907–89 ).  See also  Lawrence ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":19,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":50,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":75,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":88,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":97,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Laurence Hauberk I of Scalford was born in Stapleford, Leicestershire, England as the son of Sir Hugh Hauberk II Lord of Stapleford and Anne Bretoft. He had at least 2 sons with Margaret Attelbury. He died in 1358, in Stapleford, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"–1358":"–1358","–Female":"Surnud","–1376":"–1376","–1379":"–1379","–1343":"–1343","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1358":"1358","1259":"1259","1379":"1379","1343":"1343","1453":"1453","1376":"1376","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Stapleford, Leicestershire,England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stapleford, Leicestershire, England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, England"},"fi":{"–1358":"–1358","–Female":"Kuollut","–1376":"–1376","–1379":"–1379","–1343":"–1343","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1358":"1358","1259":"1259","1379":"1379","1343":"1343","1453":"1453","1376":"1376","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Stapleford, Leicestershire,England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stapleford, Leicestershire, Engla